On Wed, 1 Feb 2006, Old Volks Home wrote:

> Actually "Worm & Peg" Steering Boxes are what was originally installed on
> the 68-72 Bay Window.  You can use the 73-79 Worm & Roller, but a bit of
> modifying is needed I believe.  Upgrading to the later Pittman Arm is one
> thing you have to do (the output shaft is larger).

No, the later box uses different mounting holes and the "neck" is larger,
so it won't fit on an early Bay.  This has been discussed before and the
consensus is that modifying to allow use of a later box is prohibative.

Makes me be very gentle to my existing box!

